O God! Thou art my God alone;
In Thee my soul finds rest;
No other name beneath the sky
Can fill my aching breast.

When shadows fall and fears assail,
Thy presence calms the storm;
Thy guiding hand, a steady light,
Keeps me from coming harm.

Through valleys dark and mountains high,
Thy whispers soothe my way;
In every tear, in every sigh,
Thou hear'st me when I pray.

My rock, my shield, my dearest friend,
Forever let me cling;
To Thee, my worship shall ascend,
Eternal praises sing.
